.TH "scsi_normalize_sense" 9 "scsi_normalize_sense" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
scsi_normalize_sense \- normalize main elements from either fixed or descriptor sense data format into a common format.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" scsi_normalize_sense
.BI "(const u8 *sense_buffer "  ","
.BI "int sb_len "  ","
.BI "struct scsi_sense_hdr *sshdr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sense_buffer" 12
byte array containing sense data returned by device
.IP "sb_len" 12
number of valid bytes in sense_buffer
.IP "sshdr" 12
pointer to instance of structure that common
elements are written to.
.SH "NOTES"
The "main elements" from sense data are: response_code, sense_key,
asc, ascq and additional_length (only for descriptor format).

Typically this function can be called after a device has
responded to a SCSI command with the CHECK_CONDITION status.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return value:
true if valid sense data information found, else false;
